HB 927 Original 2026 Regular Session McMahen
Abstract: Provides relative to the change in Section title, the addition of a committee
position for the Medicaid Pharmaceutical and Therapeutics Committee, and the
revocation of certain allowable drug restrictions.
Present law provides that the present Section title includes peer-based prescribing and
dispensing practice patterns.
Proposed law removes peer-based prescribing and dispensing practice patterns.
Present law provides for the composure of the fifteen members appointed by the governor
to the Medicaid Pharmaceutical and Therapeutics Committee and the organizations from
which members are to be nominated from.
Proposed law adds one physician or pharmacist from each Medicaid managed care
organization to the committee.
Present law provides that the Louisiana Department of Health shall not restrict by prior
authorization any anti-retroviral prescription drugs prescribed and determined to be
medically necessary for the treatment and prevention of HIV/AIDS.
Proposed law repeals the present law which prohibits prior authorization drug restrictions
for any anti-retroviral prescription drugs prescribed and determined to be medically
necessary for the treatment and prevention of HIV/AIDS.
(Amends R.S. 46:153.3; Adds R.S. 46:153.3(D)(2)(a)(xii), and Repeals R.S. 46:153.3(C)(1))
